# Project Architecture — Ansible

## Principles

- **Idempotency is the primary correctness test.** Run the playbook twice in a row. The second run must report `changed=0`. Any task that fails this is broken, regardless of whether it produces the right output.
- Always use FQCN (`ansible.builtin.*`, `ansible.posix.*`, `community.general.*`). Never short module names.
- Prefer idempotent modules over `shell`/`command`. Use `shell`/`command` only when no module exists, and always pair with `creates:`, `removes:`, or `changed_when:`.
- One variable definition per variable — never define the same variable in multiple places.
- No plaintext secrets anywhere in the repo. Vault all credentials.
- `--check --diff` before every production apply, every time. Never apply without reviewing the diff first.

