## Project structure

### Minimum viable (single environment)
```
.
├── ansible.cfg
├── inventory                   # INI or YAML — single group
├── group_vars/
│   └── <group>/
│       ├── vars.yml            # plaintext variable names
│       └── vault.yml           # encrypted values
└── playbook.yml
```

### Production (multi-environment)
```
.
├── ansible.cfg
├── requirements.yml            # pinned roles and collections — always pin versions
├── site.yml                    # master playbook
├── inventories/
│   ├── production/
│   │   ├── hosts               # production host list
│   │   └── group_vars/
│   │       ├── all/
│   │       │   ├── vars.yml    # shared plaintext vars
│   │       │   └── vault.yml   # shared secrets (encrypted)
│   │       └── <group>/
│   │           ├── vars.yml
│   │           └── vault.yml
│   └── staging/
│       ├── hosts
│       └── group_vars/
├── roles/
│   └── <role-name>/
│       ├── tasks/main.yml
│       ├── handlers/main.yml
│       ├── defaults/main.yml   # overridable defaults — define all role vars here first
│       ├── vars/main.yml       # role-internal constants (high precedence — use sparingly)
│       ├── templates/          # .j2 Jinja2 templates
│       ├── files/              # static files
│       ├── meta/main.yml       # role dependencies
│       └── README.md           # documents all variables and defaults
└── collections/                # gitignored — installed from requirements.yml
```

