## Implementation safety rules

- Never apply without `--check --diff` first. Present the diff for human approval before any production apply.
- Never use short module names — always FQCN.
- Never use `shell:`/`command:` without `creates:`, `removes:`, or `changed_when:`.
- Never commit `.vault_pass`, `*.vault_pass`, or any plaintext credential.
- Never use `ansible-vault decrypt` → edit → `encrypt` — always use `ansible-vault edit`.
- Never use `ignore_errors: true` without a comment explaining why.
- Never define the same variable in multiple precedence levels.
- Never use `{{ }}` in `when:` conditions — `when: my_var == "value"`, not `when: "{{ my_var }}" == "value"`.
- Never use tabs in YAML — two-space indent only.
- `host_key_checking = False` only in dev/lab environments — never in production.
- Requires `Defaults !requiretty` in `/etc/sudoers` on targets when `pipelining = True`.

